III.

To Caninius Rufus of Comum are addressed letters ii. 8. iii. 7. vi. 21. vii. 18. viii. 4. ix. 33. He wrote Epic poetry, and from viii. 4. we learn that he was contemplating a poem on the Dacian war. (For the Dacian wars of Domitian and Trajan see Mommsen, Provinces of the Roman Empire, vol. i. p. 219, Merivale vii. 340.) From vii.
